Wilmington.Kalmar Nyckel:
Kalmar Nyckel (Key of Kalmar) was a Dutch-built armed merchant ship famed for carrying Swedish settlers to North America in 1638, to establish the colony of New Sweden. A replica of the ship was launched at Wilmington, Delaware, in 1997.


== History ==
Kalmar Nyckel was constructed in about 1625, and was of a design called a pinnace.
